Overview

How XSS actually works.
How to stop it from happening.

Key Learnings

It’s like SQL injection’s evil cousin, but on the client side with JavaScript.
Input validation, escaping output, CSP headers — the usual defenses.

Challenges & Reflections

This room was clean, smooth, and honestly pretty cool.
I want to come back and play with XSS payloads more on my own time.

Final Thoughts
One of the rare rooms that didn’t make me want to throw my keyboard.
